LEAD = """<strong>Responsible gold sourcing is the practice of verifying &mdash; and being able to prove &mdash; that gold comes from a legitimate mine, was traded and exported lawfully, passed through known hands, and did not finance conflict, human rights abuses or crime.</strong> It is implemented through documentation that follows the metal: origin records, licences, chain-of-custody papers and due diligence files. In today's market, responsibly sourced is not a premium category &mdash; it is the entry requirement for selling to any reputable refinery."""

BODY = """
<h2>What &ldquo;Responsible&rdquo; Means in Practice</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Known origin</strong> &mdash; the producing mine (or licensed artisanal source) is identified and its production capacity is consistent with the volumes offered.</li>
<li><strong>Lawful extraction and purchase</strong> &mdash; the source operates under valid licences; purchases from artisanal producers go through licensed aggregators.</li>
<li><strong>Clean custody</strong> &mdash; every holder of the metal between mine and refinery is identified and documented &mdash; see <a href="/knowledge/chain-of-custody-in-precious-metals/">Chain of Custody in Precious Metals</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Lawful export</strong> &mdash; royalties paid, permits issued, customs cleared &mdash; see <a href="/knowledge/gold-export-procedures-explained/">Gold Export Procedures</a>.</li>
<li><strong>No conflict or abuse financing</strong> &mdash; the supply chain avoids areas and actors where payments would fund armed groups or serious abuses, per the <a href="/knowledge/oecd-gold-supply-chain-guidance/">OECD framework</a>.</li>
<li><strong>No laundering or sanctions exposure</strong> &mdash; parties screened, funds and metal legitimate &mdash; see <a href="/knowledge/gold-aml-requirements/">Gold AML Requirements</a>.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Who Enforces It</h2>
<p>Responsibility flows backwards from the refinery. Accredited refineries must run OECD-aligned supply chain due diligence (under the LBMA Responsible Gold Guidance and equivalent hub programmes such as DMCC's in Dubai) and are audited on it annually. Refineries therefore demand evidence from exporters; exporters demand it from aggregators; aggregators from mines. Banks reinforce the chain &mdash; they finance only flows whose sourcing survives compliance review. The result: gold without provable responsible origin cannot reach a reputable refinery, a credible bank, or therefore the legitimate world market.</p>

<h2>The Seller's Evidence Pack</h2>
<p>A seller positioned for responsible sourcing review maintains, for every lot:</p>
<ol>
<li>Mine production records or licensed purchase receipts tying the lot to its source;</li>
<li>Licences at every level &mdash; mining, aggregation, export;</li>
<li>Custody documentation &mdash; sealed transfers, weights, signatures from mine to export;</li>
<li>Export documentation &mdash; assay, permits, royalty receipts, customs declarations;</li>
<li>Counterparty KYC &mdash; identity and screening records for everyone in the chain.</li>
</ol>
<p>Consistency is the test: volumes that match the source's capacity, documents that match each other, and a chain with no unexplained gaps.</p>

<h2>Example</h2>
<p>Two exporters offer similar dor&eacute; volumes. Exporter A provides mine-level production records, licensed custody at each step and clean export papers; Exporter B offers &ldquo;documents on delivery&rdquo; and a price 4% below the world market. Exporter A clears refinery due diligence in days and commands standard terms. Exporter B's offer fails before commercial discussion begins &mdash; an under-market price plus weak origin is the signature of metal that cannot enter the market lawfully. The discount is not a bargain; it is the seller pricing in their documentation problem.</p>

<h2>Artisanal Gold: Included, Not Excluded</h2>
<p>Responsible sourcing frameworks deliberately keep legitimate artisanal and small-scale mining (ASM) in the market &mdash; ASM supports millions of livelihoods. The requirement is formalisation: licensed production or aggregation, documented custody and lawful export. Buyers and facilitators who help ASM sources formalise gain access to supply competitors cannot touch &mdash; responsibly.</p>
"""

